==Crimean Tatar==
===Etymology===
Ultimately a derivation from {{der|crh|trk-pro|*yara-||to be beneficial, useful, successful}}, whence also the derivation {{m|crh|yaramay||bad}}. Equivalent to {{suffix|crh|yaramaq|alt1=yara-|gloss1=to be good enough; to please|-maz}}.
===Adjective===
{{head|crh|adjective}}
# [[bitchy]], [[perverse]], [[naughty]]
===Noun===
{{head|crh|noun}}
# [[mischievous]] [[child]], [[imp]], [[naughty]] child or animal
#*: {{quote-journal|crh|author=Гирей Баиров|title=Шамрат Халилов из деревни Стиля|journal=Голос Крыма|url=|archiveurl=|archivedate=|location=|publisher=|date=September 29, 2016|volume=38|issue=78|page=|pages=|pageurl=http://goloskrimanew.ru/shamrat-halilov-iz-derevni-stilya.html|passage=Веринъиз манъа бу '''ярамазны'''|transliteration=Veriñiz maña bu yaramaznı!|translation=Give that '''imp '''to me!}}
# [[piddler]], [[frolicker]], someone who screws around, someone who is being naughty
# [[villain]]
====Declension====
